# 101CRUISE Development Rules

## Project Vision

101CRUISE is a premium cruise planning application with an Apple-inspired design.

The application should always feel:

- Clean
- Spacious
- Professional
- Calm
- Consistent

Never introduce clutter.

---

## Technology

Frontend:
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

Hosting:
- Netlify

Planner Data:
- Supabase

CRM:
- Base44

---

## Brand Colours

Primary Green

#8DD9BF

Dark Green (text/icons only)

#245C4E

Never use any other greens unless explicitly instructed.

Progress indicators always use:

#8DD9BF

---

## Design Standards

Cards must have:

- generous spacing
- rounded corners
- consistent padding

Typography should be restrained.

Avoid oversized headings.

Avoid bold buttons unless specifically requested.

---

## Customer Page Width

All customer-facing pages and major content sections must use the shared centred outer container:

- `--planner-content-width` (1180px)
- `--planner-content-gutter` (48px)
- Reuse `.planner-shell`, `.dashboard-content-wrap`, or the shared page classes already used by Dashboard, Preparation, Packing, Budget and Documents

Do not change the global shared page width rule. Only full-bleed hero sections may span edge-to-edge.

Inside that shared shell, dense information or form pages may use a narrower centred reading column (approximately 900–980px) so labels and values remain readable. Do not replace the outer shell with a page-specific maximum width.

---

## Coding Standards

Do not rewrite unrelated code.

Modify only files required.

Reuse existing components.

Preserve current functionality.

Do not introduce duplicate CSS.

Always explain which files were changed.

---

## Development Workflow

Before making changes:

1. Read the relevant files.
2. Understand the existing implementation.
3. Make the smallest safe change.
4. Preserve existing behaviour unless instructed otherwise.

Never redesign completed modules unless requested.

The uploaded project is the source of truth.